{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781423141733,"sessionID":"ses_13ae9b23fffe3MGENYGODNFHfK","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_8vtJw5utd2YWQ9nihja58532","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/timeline.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/timeline.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Chronological Timeline [system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/timeline]\"\n3: description: \"GENERATED chronological index of 027 live-tree spec folders, newest to oldest by git activity. The recency view that is separate from folder numbers.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"027 timeline\"\n6:   - \"027 newest phase\"\n7:   - \"027 most recent spec folder\"\n8:   - \"027 chronological order\"\n9:   - \"which 027 phase is newest\"\n10: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n11: contextType: \"general\"\n12: _memory:\n13:   continuity:\n14:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement\"\n15:     last_updated_at: \"2026-06-14T07:20:50Z\"\n16:     recent_action: \"Regenerated chronological timeline from git history\"\n17:     next_safe_action: \"Use this file to find the most recent / oldest spec folder\"\n18:     completion_pct: 100\n19: ---\n20: # 027 Chronological Timeline\n21: \n22: <!-- GENERATED FILE — do not hand-edit. Regenerate: `python3 scratch/gen-timeline.py > timeline.md` (run from the 027 root). -->\n23: \n24: > **Generated:** 2026-06-14T07:20:50Z — regenerate before relying on intra-day ordering; same-day commits made\n25: > after this stamp are not reflected until the next run.\n26: > **Sort key:** git last-commit timestamp touching each folder subtree, **newest → oldest** (the\n27: > recency view), taken from one atomic `git log` snapshot. The last-active column shows\n28: > `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM` (committer local offset) because most folders share one commit day — the time\n29: > is what orders them. The `born` column is the folder's recorded `created_at` (or first git commit\n30: > of its `spec.md`), shown at day granularity.\n31: >\n32: > **Folder numbers are NOT chronology.** Numbers (`000`–`007`, child `NNN-`) encode topical/structural\n33: > identity assigned across reorg waves. This file is the *only* surface that orders by when work happened.\n34: > Phase identity → home mapping lives in [`context-index.md`](./context-index.md); the live track map lives\n35: > in [`spec.md`](./spec.md).\n36: >\n37: > **Changelog links:** §D maps every live spec folder to its packet changelog(s). Folders with none\n38: > (docs-only, research, or work consolidated into a parent rollup) show `(none)`. Phase parents link\n39: > their `-root.md` rollup, which indexes the child phase changelogs.\n40: >\n41: > **Most recent live spec folder:** `004-shared-infrastructure/008-mcp-config-alignment-reelection-default`\n42: > **Oldest live spec folder:** `005-verification-and-remediation/001-finding-remediation/sandbox-test`\n43: > **Counts:** 159 live spec folders · 0 archived (`z_archive/`).\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 0. Most recent 15 (quick answer to \"what was worked on last\")\n48: \n49: ```\n50:  1. 2026-06-14 09:09  004-shared-infrastructure/008-mcp-config-alignment-reelection-default\n51:  2. 2026-06-14 09:09  004-shared-infrastructure\n52:  3. 2026-06-14 08:55  005-verification-and-remediation\n53:  4. 2026-06-14 08:55  003-advisor-and-codegraph\n54:  5. 2026-06-14 08:55  002-memory-store-and-search\n55:  6. 2026-06-14 08:55  001-research-and-doctrine\n56:  7. 2026-06-14 08:55  000-release-cleanup/000-spec-tree-consolidation\n57:  8. 2026-06-14 08:55  005-verification-and-remediation/004-residual-design-units\n58:  9. 2026-06-14 08:55  004-shared-infrastructure/002-command-presentation-workflow-separation/008-router-consistency-hardening\n59: 10. 2026-06-14 08:55  005-verification-and-remediation/003-deep-research-remediation\n60: 11. 2026-06-14 08:55  004-shared-infrastructure/002-command-presentation-workflow-separation/007-presentation-asset-format\n61: 12. 2026-06-14 08:55  004-shared-infrastructure/002-command-presentation-workflow-separation/006-presentation-adherence-research\n62: 13. 2026-06-14 08:55  005-verification-and-remediation/002-tri-system-deep-research\n63: 14. 2026-06-14 08:55  005-verification-and-remediation/001-finding-remediation/008-doc-truth-and-test-fidelity\n64: 15. 2026-06-14 08:55  005-verification-and-remediation/001-finding-remediation/007-continuity-and-save-concurrency\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## A. Tracks — newest activity → oldest\n70: \n71: The six top-level themed tracks, ordered by most recent git activity. `Born` uses `--follow` so it\n72: traces through the reorg `git mv` history to each track's true origin.\n73: \n74: | Rank | Last active | Born | Track |\n75: |------|------------------|------------|-------|\n76: | 1 | 2026-06-14 09:09 | 2026-06-14 | `004-shared-infrastructure/` |\n77: | 2 | 2026-06-14 08:55 | 2026-06-14 | `005-verification-and-remediation/` |\n78: | 3 | 2026-06-14 08:55 | 2026-06-14 | `003-advisor-and-codegraph/` |\n79: | 4 | 2026-06-14 08:55 | 2026-06-14 | `002-memory-store-and-search/` |\n80: | 5 | 2026-06-14 08:55 | 2026-06-14 | `001-research-and-doctrine/` |\n81: | 6 | 2026-06-14 08:55 | 2026-06-10 | `000-release-cleanup/` |\n82: \n83: > Note: `000-release-cleanup/` carries a deliberate `000` prefix (cross-cutting / program\n84: > track), so it sorts first by number but is **not** the oldest by creation — see `Born` above and §B.\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## B. All live spec folders — newest → oldest\n89: \n90: Every directory containing `spec.md` under the live tree (excludes `z_archive/` and `.backup-*`\n91: snapshot dirs), flat-sorted by last git activity. `impl` = an `implementation-summary.md` is present\n92: