on-analysis.md`.\n\n  Line 102:   --format json --dir \"$PWD\" --dangerously-skip-permissions \"$(cat /tmp/<brief>.txt)\" \\\n\n  Line 103:   </dev/null > /tmp/<brief>.out.json 2> /tmp/<brief>.err.log    # run_in_background:true\n\n  Line 122: - Briefs: `/tmp/impl-011-{speckit,create,doctor}.txt`, `/tmp/xce-adoption-analysis.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/003-advisor-and-codegraph/002-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/spec.md:\n  Line 56: | **Source of truth** | `/tmp/xce-adoption-analysis.md` (ranked 027 transfer analysis, 2026-06-10) |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/004-shared-infrastructure/001-mcp-to-cli-tool-transition/001-spec-memory-cli/001-cli-core/spec.md:\n  Line 101: - Socket-path safety: default unset socket dir to `/tmp/mk-spec-memory` (35-byte path), reject paths over the 104-byte Darwin sun_path cap or require explicit TCP fallback\n\n  Line 138: | REQ-006 | Shim dist-freshness guard + short-socket-dir default | Stale dist exits 69 with rebuild hint; unset socket dir lands under /tmp/mk-spec-memory |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/review/reorg-verify/lineages/mimo/iterations/iteration-002.md:\n  Line 25: - **F006**: Local temp paths in handover.md, `handover.md:42`, References `/tmp/impl-011-{speckit,create}.out.json` — machine-local paths that would be meaningless if the handover is shared externally. Advisory only; no credential exposure.\n\n  Line 46: - Searched for home/temp paths in research outputs: no matches (except the handover /tmp/ reference)\n\n  Line 56:   \"claim\": \"handover.md references local /tmp/ paths that would be meaningless if shared externally.\",\n\n  Line 60:   \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Checked if /tmp/ paths are gitignored or excluded from sharing — they are not. Checked if handover.md is in .gitignore — it is not. However, /tmp/ is universally understood as ephemeral.\",\n\n  Line 64:   \"downgradeTrigger\": \"Already P2. Could be resolved by removing the /tmp/ reference or noting it is ephemeral.\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/004-shared-infrastructure/001-mcp-to-cli-tool-transition/001-spec-memory-cli/001-cli-core/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 47: Built a daemon-backed `spec-memory` CLI as a second IPC client over the unchanged mk-spec-memory daemon. The CLI generates its command map from `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`, validates argv-derived arguments with the existing Zod schemas, sends `tools/call` JSON-RPC frames over `daemon-ipc.sock`, auto-spawns via `mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` when the daemon probe fails, and renders `json`, `jsonl`, or text output. The shim defaults unset `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR` to `/tmp/mk-spec-memory`, rejects stale/missing dist with exit 69, and delegates to fresh `dist/spec-memory-cli.js`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/002-tri-system-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-050.md:\n  Line 12: - Detail: The research/review/context save phases call generate-context.js with /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json, but the workflow asset does not define a step that writes that structured JSON payload first. The loader requires --stdin, --json, or an existing JSON file and throws EXPLICIT_DATA_FILE_LOAD_FAILED when the file is absent, so the advertised automatic memory save depends on out-of-band behavior.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-research-and-doctrine/001-peck-teachings-adop